{{Orphan|date=September 2010}}

'''Unpaid workers''' are those who [[employment|work]] without [[wage|pay]].  These may be either members of a [[family]] or [[cooperative]]; [[conscripts]] or [[forced labour]]; [[volunteer]] workers who work for [[charity (practice)|charity]] or [[amusement]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://books.google.com/?id=q5QOAAAAQAAJ |year=1993 |title=Volunteers |isbn=9780415094276 |author=Jone L. Pearce}}</ref>; [[student]]s who take [[intern]] positions as [[work experience]]; or conventional workers who are not paid because their enterprise is short of [[money]] or subject to [[embezzlement]].

